answers.body_markdown:
It is impossible to do using two-dimensional array and [`Collection.swap()`][1]. Because it takes [`List&lt;?&gt;`][2] as an argument. Therefore it may accept a list of rows or a single row, but not the matrix itself.

However you can represent the matrix as a one-dimensional array and the code will look like:

    for (int row = 0; row &lt; size; row++) {
        for (int col = row + 1; col &lt; size; col++) {
            Collections.swap(list, row * size + col, col * size + row);
        }
    }


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Collections.html#swap-java.util.List-int-int-
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/List.html

